    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="content">
                <div class="why-section">
                                    <h2>STOP THE MEDIA CONTROL BILL</h2>

                    <h2>Why This Bill Threatens Democracy</h2>
                    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 25px; color: white; font-weight: 600;">
                        The proposed Media Control Bill would replace media self-regulation with government control, 
                        giving authorities unprecedented power to silence journalists and news outlets.
                    </p>

                    <div class="threats-grid">
                        <div class="threat-item">
                            <h3>Crushing Financial Penalties</h3>
                            <p>Individual journalists face fines up to MVR 25,000 (US$ 1,620) for not making "corrections" fast enough</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="threat-item">
                            <h3>Immediate Shutdowns</h3>
                            <p>Media outlets can be shut down indefinitely without formal court verdicts during "investigations"</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="threat-item">
                            <h3>Newsroom Raids</h3>
                            <p>"National security" clause allows the commission to enter newsrooms through police</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="threat-item">
                            <h3>Forced Apologies</h3>
                            <p>Journalists can be forced to apologize for publishing information the government deems "false"</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="threat-item">
                            <h3>Internet Censorship</h3>
                            <p>Commission can block websites and target social media posts and content creators</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="threat-item">
                            <h3>Rigged Oversight</h3>
                            <p>President appoints 3 of 7 commission members, while parliament can dismiss elected media representatives</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="action-section">
                <h2>TAKE ACTION NOW</h2>
                <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 30px; font-weight: 600; color: black;">
                    Email the Independent Institutions Committee to reject this dangerous bill. 
                    Click below to open your email client with a pre-written message. You can customize it with your name and organization before sending.
                </p>

                <a href="#" id="emailButton" class="email-btn">
                    Send Email to Parliament Committee
                </a>

                <div class="voted-carousel">
                    <div class="carousel-track" id="carouselTrack">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="hashtags">
                <span class="hashtag">#UluBillOut</span>
                <span class="hashtag">#CTRLBillBeyrukurey</span>
                <span class="hashtag">#CTRLehNukureveyne</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <p>
                Learn more about the bill: 
                <a href="https://maldivesindependent.com/politics/maldives-media-stands-firm-in-standoff-over-control-bill-fde2" target="_blank">
                    Maldives Independent Coverage
                </a>
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.9rem; opacity: 0.7;">
                This is an independent citizen initiative to defend press freedom
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        // Email button functionality
        document.getElementById('emailButton').addEventListener('click', function(e) {
            e.preventDefault();
            
            const subject = encodeURIComponent('URGENT: Reject the Media Control Bill - Defend Press Freedom');
            
            const body = encodeURIComponent(`My name is [YOUR NAME].

I call on the Independent Institutions Committee chair Hussain Riza Adam to reject the Media Control Bill.

This bill poses a severe threat to press freedom and democratic governance in the Maldives. The proposed legislation would:

• Allow indefinite shutdown of media outlets without court verdicts
• Impose crushing fines on individual journalists (up to MVR 25,000)
• Enable government raids of newsrooms under "national security" pretexts
• Force journalists to apologize for information deemed "false" by authorities
• Block websites and censor social media content
• Replace media self-regulation with government control

The vague definitions of "fake news" and "false information" are ripe for abuse and could lead to criminal prosecution of journalists simply for doing their job.

I urge the committee to:
1. Reject this bill entirely
2. Protect constitutional press freedoms
3. Maintain the current self-regulatory framework
4. Engage in genuine consultation with media stakeholders

Press freedom is fundamental to democracy. This bill must not pass.

#UluBillOut
#CTRLBillBeyrukurey  
#CTRLehNukureveyne

Respectfully,
[YOUR NAME]`);

            const mailtoLink = `mailto:indep.institutions_committee@majlis.gov.mv?subject=${subject}&body=${body}`;
            
            window.location.href = mailtoLink;
        });

        // Carousel functionality
